f\in L^1(\mu)
\left|\int_X f~d\mu\right| = \int_X |f|~d\mu
\exists
\beta
|f|=\beta f
X
\left|\int_X f~d\mu\right| =\beta\int_X f~d\mu
\beta
|f|-\beta f \geq 0
|f| =\beta f
\int_X |f|~d\mu = \beta \int_X f~d\mu \implies \int_X \left(|f|-\beta f\right)~d\mu =0
\int_X |f| - \beta f = 0
\int_X (|f| - Re(\beta f)) = 0
|\beta| = 1
x
Re(\beta f(x)) \leq |f(x)|
\beta f(x) = |f(x)|
\int_X (|f| - Re(\beta f)) = 0
\beta f(x) = |f(x)|
x
\int_X \beta f(x) = \beta \int_X f(x)
